<h1>Foreign Investment Review Board (FIRB) approval</h1>
</sub_heading>
</div>
<div class="text parbase">
<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><a href="/Net/Documentum/regulatory-requirements/default.aspx">Back to Regulatory Requirements</a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Under Australia’s foreign investment framework, foreign persons generally need to apply for foreign investment approval before purchasing residential real estate in Australia</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> FIRB approval are required to be obtained before they can acquire an interest in residential real estate. (Refer <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-excluded-borrowers.aspx">Eligible Borrowers </a> for exemption &amp; <a href="http://firb.gov.au/">http://firb.gov.au/</a> for current requirements)</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">An interest in residential real estate can include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">signing an unconditional contract agreeing to purchase a property;</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">signing an unconditional contract agreeing to purchase a share of a dwelling (such as joint tenants or tenants in common with any number of other people)</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>What you need know</b></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">If any one of the Home Loan applicants are not a Permanent Resident, then Foreign Investment Review Board (FIRB) approval may be required prior to loan approval</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">For Specified Temporary Resident &amp; Overseas citizens refer to <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-excluded-borrowers.aspx">Eligible Borrowers </a>for eligibility</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The FIRB approval may vary for specified temporary residents and overseas citizen. FIRB Condition may prohibit customer from buying a new dwelling/vacant residential land or a second hand or established dwelling</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Specified Temporary residents may apply to purchase one established dwelling to use as a residence while they live in Australia however they may be restricted by FIRB to acquire established dwellings to rent out or for use as a holiday home.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">When a FIRB approval is provided, ensure the following information in the FIRB approval is aligned to the application:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Applicant's Name</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Security address / Property being purchased</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Loan purpose (e.g. investment versus owner occupied)</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Property classification / sub classification (e.g. new dwelling or established dwelling or vacant land)</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Any other restrictions / conditions applied by the FIRB</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">If FIRB Exemption Certificate is provided, ensure that the name on the Exemption certificate is the same at the applicants.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Please refer to   <a href="http://firb.gov.au/">http://firb.gov.au/</a> for current requirements</span></p>
<p> </p>
